I want to know why all my ads have not been approved. I have changed them many times. I suspect that this is the platform targeting me.

I'm sorry to hear about the trouble you're having with your ads. Ad rejection reasons can vary, such as incorrect conversion tracking setup for tCPA campaigns or typographical errors. Ad Support should inform you of the specific reasons via email. I recommend checking the advertising policy before submitting ads to ensure compliance. If you need further assistance, please email adsupport@newsbreak.com.

He always reminds me: Reason for rejection: Advertising policy violation - The brand name in your ad is inconsistent with the product you are promoting. Please make necessary adjustments to make your brand name consistent with your product. But I have changed it again and again, and the same advertiser as me has passed the review. Even our products and ads are exactly the same. This is your discrimination and discrimination against me.

I understand your frustration with the repeated rejections. It's important to ensure that the brand name in your ad matches the product being promoted to comply with our advertising policy. If you believe your ad complies and the rejection was a misunderstanding, you can submit an appeal by emailing adsupport@newsbreak.com. They will be able to provide more detailed assistance and review your case.
